description.narrative: The development objectives of the Water Sector Improvement Project are: (i) to improve irrigation service deliveryon a sustainable basis so as to increase productivity of irrigated agriculture in the Nagarjuna Sagar Scheme, and (ii) to strengthen the institutional capacity for multi-sectoral planning, development and management of water resources in Andhra Pradesh and Telangana.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :PA Schedule-Section I-A (2) | Description :Andhra Pradesh shall at all times throughout Project implementation,staff andmaintain, in a manner satisfactory to the Bank, the Project Preparation andManagement Unit within I&CADD. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA Schedule-Section I-A (4) | Description :Andhra Pradesh shall cause its I&CADD, with the assistance of wateruser organizations, to carry out the participatory rehabilitation and modernization activities under Part A of the Project. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA Schedule-Section I-B (1) | Description :Andhra Pradesh shall take necessary actions to ensure that adequateallocations are included in the state budget for annual counterpart funds, and said allocations are released to the Project. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA Schedule-Section I-B (2) | Description :Andhra Pradesh shall take necessary actions to ensure adequateallocations in the State budget to satisfy the Nagarjuna Sagar Scheme's full annual operational and maintenance requirements. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA Schedule-Section I-C (1) | Description :Andhra Pradesh shall take necessary actions to ensure the existenceandfunctioning of water user organizations at all levels within the Nagarjuna SagarScheme. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :PA Schedule-Section I-C (2) | Description :Andhra Pradesh shall take necessary actions to operationalize theAndhra Pradesh Water Resources RegulatoryCommission. | Due Date :31-Dec-2011

Finance Agreement :PA Schedule-Section I-C (3) | Description :Andhra Pradesh shall cause the provision of bulk water supply towater user organizations according to their respective allocationsunder the Nagarjuna Sagar Scheme, as determined by the APWRRC. |Due Date :30-Jun-2012

Finance Agreement :PA Schedule-Section II-A (3) | Description :Andhra Pradesh shall establish within six months of the EffectiveDate, and thereafter maintain at all times during the implementation of the Project, an external monitoring & evaluation agency. |Due Date :28-Feb-2011
